Quote:  One of the most striking examples of the various fundraising methods was the formation of the 'Girls Khaki Brigade' in Wellington. ... The 'Girls Khaki Brigade' were to help promote and entrust contributions to the "More Men and Patriotic Funds."  Properly known as the 'Young Ladies Contingent' the unit was known by a number of variations at the time.
